						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 15 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> deposited with a <hi rend="italic">Śivabrāhmaṇa</hi> of the temple of Ūrbāgaṅkoṇḍaruḷiya-Nāyaṉār, for burning a lamp in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> on the <hi rend="italic">“tirumalai”</hi> during the evening service of the god, by Mūvāyirattoruvaṉ Śōlaippirāṉ a merchant of Kōmar. The monthly interest on the amount is said to be 3/8 <hi rend="italic">kāśu i.e.</hi>, at the rate of 2(1/2) per cent.</p>						

						</summary>
